reviewText: The description says "in this Airplane!-like send up of modern healthcare". The problem is that movie has already been done. The movie was called Young Doctors in Love, it was hilarious and in the spirit of Airplane!. The closest Robodoc comes to Airplane! is one joke it ripped off, from Airplane!.Robodoc is devoid of laughs, snickers, or even a smirk. The jokes it tries were beaten to death long ago. If you watch this movie you will not get that part of your life you wasted back.National Lampoon is very clearly done making good movies. Was the last one Vacation?
Title: National Lampoon Presents ROBODOC

reviewText: This was a fun movie.  Not realistic but it never clammed to be realistic.  Takes a new spin on the healthcare/legal industry and how out of touch it is. Not a deep thinking movie but fun for a cold day that you want to spend on the couch at home.

reviewerName: The Movie Guy "Movies from A to Z"
reviewText: Certainly this is one of National Lampoon's better efforts here of late. Considering the stupidity they have been coming out with, this stupid movie had a lot more going for it. It has less gratuitous nudity than expected by the cover. It also stars David Faustino's ex-wife (not the babe on the cover.)
Title: National Lampoon Presents ROBODOC
